<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n38220b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38220b">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38220b"> 220(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> cucurbit belly / capital head</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Avicenna, who died in <year>A.H.</year> 428 = 1036, nearly two hundred years before we read of distillation in Europe, compared the human body with an alembic, <mark>the belly being the cucurbit, and the head the capital</mark>: &mdash; he forgot an important difference but <i>n&apos;importe</i>. <small> Richard F. Burton, &ldquo;Terminal Essay&rdquo;, <a name="RBTE1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#RBTE1"><cite title="source">The Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night</cite></a> (n.d.) X, 87</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
